A Federal High Court, Abuja has ordered the 16 lawmakers from Ebonyi to vacate their seats after their defection from the Peoples Democratic Party to the All Progressives Congress.The court declared their defection unlawful, unconstitutional, null and void and ordered them to immediately vacate their offices. In his judgment, Justice Inyang Ekwo ordered the state assembly members to stop parading themselves as the peopleâ€™s representatives after dumping the party on which platform they were elected.Justice Ekwo ordered that all monies collected from the top period of their defection to the judgment date must be recovered from them.Some of the sacked lawmakers include Odefa Obasi Odefa, Victor Chukwu, Kingsley Ikoro, Joseph Ununu, Nkemka Okoro, among others.Recall that Justice Ekwo had on January 19, fixed today for the judgment in the suit filed by the PDP against the governor and his deputy.The court had earlier sacked the state governor, Dave Umahi and his deputy, Eric Igwe, citing same reason as defecting to the APC from the PDP.